===2010 census===
As of the [[census]] of 2010, there were 80 people, 50 households, and 24 families residing in the town. The [[population density]] was {{convert|421.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 100 housing units at an average density of {{convert|526.3|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the town was 100.0% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]].

There were 50 households, of which 4.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 48.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, and 52.0% were non-families. 46.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 34% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 1.60 and the average family size was 2.13.

The median age in the city was 70 years. 2.5% of residents were under the age of 18; 5.1% were between the ages of 18 and 24; 5.1% were from 25 to 44; 28.9% were from 45 to 64; and 58.8% were 65 years of age or older. The gender makeup of the town was 52.5% male and 47.5% female.

