As of the [[census]] of 2000, there were 114 people, 65 households, and 36 families residing in the town. The population density was {{convert|638.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 98 housing units at an average density of {{convert|549.1|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 99.12% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]] and 0.88% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]].

There were 65 households, out of which 4.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 47.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 6.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 43.1% were non-families. 40.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 29.2% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 1.75 and the average family size was 2.24.

In the town, the population was spread out, with 6.1% under the age of 18, 5.3% from 18 to 24, 16.7% from 25 to 44, 27.2% from 45 to 64, and 44.7% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 63 years. For every 100 females, there were 90.0 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 91.1 males.

The median income for a household in the town was $20,938, and the median income for a family was $28,750. Males had a median income of $21,563 versus $13,333 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $13,912. There were 11.1% of families and 13.9% of the population living below the [[poverty line]], including no under eighteens and 15.2% of those over 64.

